name: r-cloudos
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.3.0" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-cloudos
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/cloudos_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/cloudos/cloudos_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 41e479905f45439904ae2c7c560dd644990bfc4bf01a024f619bdf78ce1568e5

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-dplyr >=1.0.0
    - r-ggplot2
    - r-httr
    - r-jsonlite
    - r-rappdirs
    - r-tibble
    - r-tidyr
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-dplyr >=1.0.0
    - r-ggplot2
    - r-httr
    - r-jsonlite
    - r-rappdirs
    - r-tibble
    - r-tidyr

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('cloudos')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('cloudos')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/lifebit-ai/cloudos
  license: MIT
  summary: The 'CloudOS' client library for R makes it easy to interact with CloudOS <https://cloudos.lifebit.ai/> in the R environment for analysis.
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
